    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-10-26T22:43:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-10-26T22:43:00-05:00" n="59"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d59">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB/10–2647: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-10-26T22:43:00-05:00"
                            >October 26, 1947—10:43 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1095. For Bohlen from Ross. Following is text of draft compromise resolution
                    worked out today by the Australian, Canadian and French delegations and
                    telephoned to me this evening.<note n="1" xml:id="d59fn1">For official text, see
                            <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> (II), <hi rend="italic">First
                            Committee</hi>, p. 577, annex 13<hi rend="italic">f</hi>.</note> This
                    will be discussed in delegation meeting Monday morning.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d59fn2">October 27.</note> The three delegations concerned plan to
                    introduce this resolution at the outset of the 11:00 meeting.</p>
                <pb facs="0126" n="96" xml:id="pg_96"/>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“<hi rend="smallcaps">Whereas</hi>
                    </p>
                    <p>In the Charter of the UN, the peoples expressed their determination to save
                        succeeding generations from the scourge of war which twice in our lifetime
                        has brought untold sorrow to mankind, and to practice tolerance and live
                        together in peace with one another as good neighbors;</p>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Whereas</hi>
                    </p>
                    <p>The Charter also calls for the promotion of universal respect for, and
                        observance of, fundamental freedoms including freedom of expression, all
                        members having pledged themselves in Article 56 to take joint and separate
                        action for such observance of fundamental freedoms</p>
                    <p>The <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>
                    </p>
                    <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">condemns</hi> all forms of propaganda, in
                            whatsoever countries conducted, which is either designed or likely to
                            provoke or encourage any threat to the peace, breach of the peace, or
                            act of aggression.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">requests</hi> the Government of each member to take
                            appropriate steps: <list>
                                <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                                <item>To promote by all means of publicity and propaganda available
                                    to them friendly relations among nations based on the purposes
                                    and principles of the Charter;</item>
                                <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                                <item>To encourage the dissemination of all information designed to
                                    give expression to the undoubted desire of all peoples for
                                    peace;</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">directs</hi> that this resolution be communicated
                            to the forthcoming Conference on Freedom of Information with a
                            recommendation that the conference consider methods for carrying out the
                            purposes of this resolution.”</item>
                    </list>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed> [Ross] <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
